==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hopping
<hw>Hop"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of one who,
or that which, hops; a jumping, frisking, or dancing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hopping Dick</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a thrush
of Jamaica (<spn>Merula leucogenys</spn>), resembling the English
blackbird in its familiar manners, agreeable song, and dark
plumage.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hopping</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hopping
<hw>Hop"ping</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 3rd <er>Hop</er>.]</ety>
<def>A gathering of hops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hopple</ent>⟦br⟧
